The paper deals with the problem of performing frequent itemset mining on transaction databases while satisfying differential privacy. This problem is closely related to database systems (cs.DB), privacy and security (cs.CR), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), machine learning (cs.LG), and information theory (cs.IT). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper, ordered from most to least likely.
